# 👁️ Unveil – Bypass Paywalls, Unlock Copying, and Clean the Web

**Unveil** is a stealthy Chrome extension that gives you full control over restricted websites.  
It removes overlays, re-enables copy/paste, toggles dark mode, and **bypasses soft paywalls like The New York Times** — all in one click.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 📰 **New York Times Paywall Bypass**  
- 🔓 **Enable Copy & Paste on Restricted Pages**  
- 🌑 **Dark Mode for Any Website**   
- ⚡ **One-Click “Toggle All” Unlock**  
- 🎨 **Custom CSS Injection**

---

## 🔧 Installation

1. Download or clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/unveil-extension.git
   ```
2. Open Chrome and go to:  
   `chrome://extensions`
3. Enable **Developer mode** (toggle at the top right)
4. Click **“Load Unpacked”** and select the `unveil-extension` folder
5. The 👁️ **Unveil** icon should now appear in your toolbar

---

## 📖 How to Use

### 📰 1. Bypass The New York Times Paywall

Unveil removes soft overlays and blur filters that hide NYT content.

1. Open any NYT article (e.g. https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/28/technology/example.html)
2. Click the **👁️ Unveil** extension icon
3. Click the **“Find Blocked Elements”** button
4. Done — overlay removed, full article revealed, scroll restored

✅ Works on most NYT articles that use soft paywalls  
❌ Will not work if content is fully removed server-side (hard paywalls)

---

### 🔓 2. Enable Copy & Paste

1. Go to a site that blocks right-click or text selection
2. Click the **Unveil** icon
3. Click **“Enable Copy & Paste”**
4. You can now highlight, copy, and paste like normal

Perfect for:
- Blogs with anti-copy scripts  
- Online learning platforms  
- Preview-only Google Docs  
- Docs with disabled context menus

---

### 🌑 3. Toggle Dark Mode

1. Open any bright/light website
2. Click the **Unveil** icon
3. Click **“Toggle Dark Mode”**
4. Page gets converted to a clean, readable dark theme

Great for:
- Reading at night  
- Reddit, Substack, Notion, docs, etc.

---

### ⚡ 4. Use “Toggle All”

1. Click the **Unveil** icon
2. Press **“Toggle All”**

This will:
- Enable copy/paste  
- Reveal hidden elements  
- Activate dark mode  
- Show a popup summary of elements modified

Great when you want full control fast.

---

### 🖌 5. Inject Custom CSS

1. Paste your custom CSS into the textarea inside the popup
2. Press **“Inject Custom CSS”**
3. Your styles will apply instantly to the current page

---

## 🎯 Keyboard Shortcut

- Windows: `Ctrl + Shift + U`  
- Mac: `Cmd + Shift + U`

→ Instantly runs Toggle All without clicking the popup.

---

## 🔐 Permissions

Unveil uses the following permissions:

- `activeTab`: Modify the current tab
- `scripting`: Inject scripts/styles
- `tabs`: Track the active tab for execution
- `storage`: (future) Save per-site preferences

> 🔒 Unveil runs 100% locally — no tracking, no data collection, no cloud calls.

---

